Landing page must remain dark with a minimal navbar, while authenticated inner pages show theme controls without a flash on load.

- **Prepaint theme bootstrap**
  - Insert synchronous theme selection in `<head>` and skip on landing pages.
- **Navbar visibility rules**
  - Hide toggle/notifications/logout on landing; show them only for authenticated inner pages.
- **Landing-only dark mode**
  - Add `landing-page` body class and enforce dark CSS variables for that scope.
- **Theme persistence**
  - Skip JS theme initialization on landing and default toggle state safely.

```html
<script>
  (function() {
    var isLanding = window.location.pathname === '/' ||
                    window.location.pathname === '/index' ||
                    document.body.classList.contains('landing-page');
    if (isLanding) return;
    var theme = localStorage.getItem('theme') || 'dark';
    document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', theme);
  })();
</script>
```
